    <div class="block__content">
      <p>Street Support Network is a central online resource around homelessness in a city, currently available in Greater Manchester,
        Leeds, Bradford, Bournemouth, Portsmouth & Liverpool, with other cities keen to join.</p>
      <p>We have a simple mission - to make it easier for people who are homeless to get the help they need...</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="/find-help/">Find Help</a>: See exactly when and where support is available, and where there are gaps.</li>
        <li>
          <a href="/give-help/">Give Help</a>: See what is needed across all organisations - volunteer, offer items, or donate.</li>
        <li>
          <a href="http://news.streetsupport.net/">News</a>: Learn about homelessness in the city through stories, information, and news updates.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We make it easier for the local network of services to collaborate, co-ordinate and provide better support for people
        experiencing homelessness, and we make it easier for citizens and businesses to do something to help. Many small,
        co-ordinated actions add up to a big difference to homeless people in the city.</p>
      <p>Our long term vision is a place-driven citizen-led support network, with people with personal lived experience of homelessness
        at the heart of everything we do.</p>
    </div>

