      <h2 class="h2">Our Team</h2>
      <p>We have a core team of 6 people based in Manchester, 3 of us have lived experience of homelessness. Each city also has a network co-ordinator, supported by local organisations and volunteers.</p>
      <a href="/about/our-team/" class="btn btn--brand-d btn--in-copy">
        <span class="btn__text">About our team</span>
      </a>

      <p>We use research, co-production, human centered design and creative technology to develop online tools that make it
        easier for people experiencing homelessness to get help. We also facilitate discussion and co-production, and work
        behind the scenes to connect the network. Here is a little story of where this idea came from:
        <a href="/about/how-this-started/">How this started.</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="h2">Our Organisation</h2>
      <p>We are a not for profit company, currently waiting for our official charity status. We have been funded so far by donations
        from local philanthropists, friends, small grants, a loan from KeyFund, and business sponsorship. We always pay at
        least the real living wage for the area. We are an open and transparent organisation, so please get in touch if you
        have any further questions.</p>
      <p>In order to continue to develop and improve this central resource, and to facilitate change through the network, we
        are looking for businesses to sponsor us to help grow out team, providing more opportunities for people who have
        experienced homelessness. If you are interested in supporting us, please contact Gary at
        <a href="mailto:gary@streetsupport.net">gary@streetsupport.net</a>, or on 07824 667709.</p>
     
      <h2 class="h2">Our Network</h2>
      <p>We work in partnership with people experiencing homelessess, charities and voluntary groups, public and private sector,
        and concerned citizens. We work together to co-produce new features to meet the needs of those who will use them,
        and are continually improving the site based on user feedback. In addition to providing the online network, we also
        work behind the scenes to connect people and facilitate collaborative workshops.</p>

